To anybody reading this and thinking "aww so sad this is how cows are treated in the dairy industry" 1.) This is a propaganda doujin written by a vegan. 2.) Baby cows cannot distinguish the difference between their mothers milk and artificial milk, but are always allowed to drink after being born to attain a colostrum. In no way do they wile away in sorrow wishing they had their mothers milk, and if you think this is abusive for some reason remember many other animals are bottle fed, not just livestock. 3.) This doujin is extremely anthropomorphic. Animals do not perceive the world this way, they are not mini humans. 4.) Cows in heat will be violently bred by bulls, that's at least accurately portrayed in this doujin. This is why most farms utilize artificial insemination; it's safer and far less stressful on the cow! Anybody still questioning the care of farm animals? I'd advise you to visit a real farm instead of watching fake or misleading videos online. Don't fall for this shit.
